The Folios are the most complete surviving record of Ledger Kingdom water law and Keeper astronomical science accessible in the corridor.
Midgaard's Magistrate Ledgerhouse uses Water Court accounting methods as historical precedent for property-boundary and resource-allocation disputes.
The Charter of Passage inscriptions are cited in Continuity doctrine as pre-institutional rights that survive governance change.
Midgaard's Violet Compact registry primacy doctrine contrasts with the Charter's self-executing absolute right, which required no registration for legal standing.

