Great Oasis witness-seal formulas appear in adapted form in Mafdet's dual-attestation cargo documentation, preserving the four-witness format with maritime categories added.
Cargo bearing Great Oasis witness marks receives preferential Mafdet treatment — faster processing, lower insurance rates — because the Water Court's authentication reputation extends across the corridor.
The Ledger Houses' notation system descends from the Water Court's Littoral Branch extension, making Mafdet's commercial culture a direct scribal descendant of oasis water-law.

